Text:
@lyledal This is a perfect question for our #VisionsOfVenus 
@TwitterSpaces
! In addition to the Parker Solar Probe findings, we'll be talking about the future Venus missions VERITAS, DAVINCI and EnVision. Join us? https://t.co/SSxUFXzJXm

@Prdsta_ @NASAWebb Right? @NASAWebb is set to look at the first galaxies, planets around other suns, maybe even the building blocks of life elsewhere in our universe.

If you're feeling inspired, show us what you think the mission will find and tag it #UnfoldTheUniverse. 

https://t.co/HAJ634qXWY

Too excited to sleep? We get it.

@NASAWebb – the world’s most powerful space telescope – is set to lift off Dec. 25 at 7:20am ET (12:20 UTC). Live NASA TV coverage begins at 6am ET (11:00 UTC): https://t.co/z1RgZwQkWS

#UnfoldTheUniverse https://t.co/Y1c1VLraeq

In 2022, we plan to launch four missions into space to help us study, understand and protect our home planet. 

@NASAEarth has the details on EMIT, SWOT, TROPICS and @NOAA's JPSS-2: https://t.co/Ss77xT5Das

#AGU21 https://t.co/e9GvfPRM6R

@Handbasket_ @ulalaunch You'll often find us out to launch. 😋

Our launches have something to do with your lunches (breakfasts and dinners, too). 

See how NASA plays a role in the food on your table: https://t.co/aeYABlgAk9

@KSivachukArt @TwitterSpaces @NASAUniverse Find out more about these two X-ray 'scopes and their study of black holes:
- @chandraxray https://t.co/cnKqG4po3s
- NuSTAR https://t.co/kLuTEoODqu

Q: What are you most excited for — the spacewalks, the science, or flying the Crew Dragon?

A: Yes. 

@AstroMarshburn expresses excitement for his third spaceflight to the @Space_Station with the #Crew3 mission: https://t.co/rFWpS6wBlE
